description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Diabetes Specialist Dietitian to join the Nutrition and Dietetics service at Airedale NHS Foundation trust, due to the retirement of the existing post-holder. The post will offer you a range of clinical experience in adult diabetes, working mostly in primary care across the beautiful and diverse population of Airedale, Wharfedale and Craven. The post includes supporting adults with all types of diabetes in both hospital and community settings, working with a diverse multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There will be opportunities to deliver diabetes structured education for both Type 1 and Type 2 diabetes, and to train other healthcare professionals. The post holder will be trained as an X-PERT educator if you do not already hold the accreditation. We have an exciting collaboration in place with the Modality primary care network to develop and deliver a low carbohydrate diet programme in the local area, and the post holder will contribute to this innovative and exciting area of practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Across the district we have a diverse population, in terms of both age and ethnicity in both rural and urban communities. We are looking for a dietitian who is passionate about diabetes care and improving the patient experience and outcomes. Team work and integrated working is a core component of the philosophy of local diabetes care delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide you with opportunities to develop your skills and knowledge in diabetes dietetics within a supportive, learning environment. You will be provided with an individualised induction and training programme, alongside regular practice supervision from senior dietitians. There is excellent clerical support, IT access and a strong commitment to continuing professional development, clinical effectiveness and audit. We provide B and C placements for student dietitians and work closely with Leeds Beckett University.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Airedale NHS Foundation Trust is an acute services Trust based in Keighley, West Yorkshire. We are situated on the edge of the beautiful Yorkshire Dales and only 10 miles from the multicultural city of Bradford.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We encourage prospective candidates to visit the department, meet our team and learn about the opportunities on offer to develop your dietetic career.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
